<p style="text-align: justify;">Bale then starred in the historical epic <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1410063/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>The Flower of the Wars</strong> (2011)</a>. In addition to that, he again played Bruce Wayne in the third and final trilogy of Batman Series <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1345836/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>The Dark Knight Rises</strong> (2012)</a>. He also performed in thriller <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1206543/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Out of the Furnance</strong> (2013)</a> and the drama comedy<a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1800241/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> <strong>American Hustle</strong> (2013)</a> for which he gained 43 lb. (20 kg) and also gone bald for it.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Then he starred in a biblical epic <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1528100/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Exodus: Gods and Kings </strong>(</a>2014)Â and in Adam McKayâ€™s biopic <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1596363/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>The Big Short</strong> (2015)</a>.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Personal life</strong></p>
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-247" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/gf-201x300.jpg" alt="" width="310" height="463" />
<p style="text-align: justify;">Bale lives in Los Angeles with his family. He married Sandra Blazic a model, make-up artist and personal assistant to actress Winona Ryder. They have two kids together: daughter Emmaline and son Joseph.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Bale actively supports Sea Shephard Conservation Society and World Wildlife Fund and is also on Board of trustees of Dian Fossey Gorilla Fund.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Major achievements</strong></p>
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-248" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/oscar-240x300.jpg" alt="" width="395" height="494" />
<p style="text-align: justify;">Christianâ€™s role in <strong>Empire of Sons</strong> bagged him <strong>Best Performer by a Juvenile actor</strong> from the <strong>National Board of Review of Motion Pictures</strong>. He also won <strong>Saturn award</strong> <strong>for Best Actor</strong> and <strong>the Best Hero Awards</strong> at the 2006 MTV Movies Awards for his movie Batman Begins. Moreover, he won the <strong>Oscar Award</strong>, the <strong>Golden Globe Award</strong> and the <strong>Academy Award</strong> for <strong>Best Supporting actor</strong> and other 30 awards for his movie <strong>The Fighter</strong>. On top of that, in 2011 he was listed in the <strong>top 100 most influential people</strong> <strong>in the world</strong> by Time Magazine.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Recent Projects</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Bale is set to star in musical film <strong>Song to Song</strong>, a period drama <strong>Hostiles </strong>and also remake of the epic adventure fantasy movie <strong>Jungle Book</strong>.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Hats off to the dedication, loyalty and passion of Christian Bale for his profession and we hope to see more of him in the upcoming days!!!</p>
